&lt;h1 id="persuade-xor-discover"&gt;Persuade xor Discover&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;September 2009&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When meeting people you don&amp;rsquo;t know very well, the convention is to seem extra friendly. You smile and say &amp;ldquo;pleased to meet you,&amp;rdquo; whether you are or not. There&amp;rsquo;s nothing dishonest about this. Everyone knows that these little social lies aren&amp;rsquo;t meant to be taken literally, just as everyone knows that &amp;ldquo;Can you pass the salt?&amp;rdquo; is only grammatically a question.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Putting Ideas into Words</title><link>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/words/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_en/words/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;→ &lt;a href="https://linguage.github.io/paul_graham/essays_zh/words/"&gt;中文版&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
